  "description": "A Torus knot at (1,6) — the near-unknot. pqScale=0.707, the lowest asymmetry of any standard torus winding, approaching symmetric coupling. The (1,6) torus is one crossing away from an unknot — barely knotted, almost free. macroKnot=0.8 pushes through Torus toward Solomon, but the near-unknot starting topology means the interpolated matrix never fully entangles. What results is a strange deep pressure: partial coupling from a near-unknot blending into two-ring Solomon architecture. Low filter, slow LFO on braid depth at 0.01 Hz — a breathing cycle so slow it barely registers as motion. The abyssal zone where pressure distorts topology.",
